        <section class="row project-card" id="project-enviro">
          <aside class="project-img col-lg-2">
            <img src="/static/images/enviro-logo.png" class="project-logo" alt="Enviro">
          </aside>
          <section class="project-about col-lg-9">
            <article class="project-description">
              <p>Currently in alpha stage, Enviro is a personalized air pollution monitoring application built for India in wake of the recent air pollution
                crisis in Delhi. The app provides real-time air pollution infomation from government sites as well as US consulates
                in India. Users can report any breathing discomfort that they may have at any point in time within India on the app
                to detect patterns and get a rough of idea which pollutants they are likely to have senstivitiy towards. The app is
                available on the Windows Universal Platform and will be extended to Android once it has matured. The app is certified by the Govt. of India.
              </p>
            </article>
            <nav class="project-actions">
              <a href="#"><div class="button-white button-project"><span>Coming Soon ➔</span></div></a>
            </nav>
          </section>
        </section>

        <section class="row project-card" id="project-stopwatch">
          <aside class="project-img col-lg-2">
            <img src="/static/images/stopwatch-logo.png" class="project-logo" alt="SISOS">
          </aside>
          <section class="project-about col-lg-9">
            <article class="project-description" id="sisos-description">
              <p>One of my first projects, 'Stopwatch by Dcode IN' is a simple stopwatch app that helps the user keep track of
                the time they take for a particular activity. A bright and illuminated time panel at the top of the app shows 
                the time taken to the nearest second while, a dark secondary panel under the time panel shows the laps that the user logged during his/her
                activity. <i>Note: <b>'Dcode IN'</b> is my publisher name on the Windows Store.</i>
              </p>
            </article>
             <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/store/apps/9njmzjbszkhv"><div class="button-white button-project"><span>View in Store ➔</span></div></a>
          </section>
        </section>


        <h3 style="color: grey; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 5.8%;">Web Applications</h3>

        <section class="row project-card" id="project-sisos">
          <aside class="project-img col-lg-2">
            <img src="/static/images/sisos-logo.png" class="project-logo" alt="SISOS">
          </aside>
          <section class="project-about col-lg-9">
            <article class="project-description" id="sisos-description">
              <p>SISOS was a web application that I created for my school to monitor student attendence beyond standard school hours.
                The application works by demanding students to login using their mobile devices within 20 mins of the 
                end of standard school hours and logging out using the same credentials at a kiosk present at all exits.
                Allowed administrative staff can log into the application using their accounts to view a list of students
                present in school at the time. The application was used as an interim solution before smart cards were 
                introduced at the school.
              </p>
            </article>
            <a href="#"><div class="button-white button-project" data-toggle="modal" data-target=".detailsModal-universal"><span>Screenshots ➔</span></div></a>
          </section>
        </section>

